General.Name: Control Bionics Ltd
General.Description: Control Bionics Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the research, development, commercialization, and sale of assistive communications technology systems in Australia and North America. The company offers NeuroNode Trilogy and NeuroNode3 systems that allow people with speech and movement difficulties to control a computer for speech generation, electronic communications, entertainment, and external control of other devices. It also provides Cosmos Connect, a device to control a range of devices, including wheelchairs, dining robots, and gaming systems; Uno Touch, a speech generating device; and other sensors for multiple applications. The company was formerly known as Control Bionics Holdings Pty Limited and changed its name to Control Bionics Limited in September 2020. Control Bionics Limited was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Camberwell, Australia.
